        <p class="text-xs leading-relaxed text-charcoal/70" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">
          Brian grew up in Connecticut, where, like many chefs, his first job was washing dishes. This marked the start of his epic culinary journey. After graduating from the Culinary Institute of America, Brian traveled the world working for global hospitality luminaries such as Charlie Palmer, Thomas Keller, Jos&eacute; Andr&eacute;s, and Daniel Boulud. In 2019, he moved to New York after transitioning from Executive Chef at Bar Boulud to that same position at Boulud Sud.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xs leading-relaxed text-charcoal/70 mt-2" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">
          When the pandemic shut down restaurants across the country, thousands of chefs and hospitality workers suddenly found themselves out of work. Instead of watching the industry collapse, Brian evolved. He created Executive Chefs At Home (ECAH) to help his peers find stability and meaningful work during an unprecedented crisis&mdash;and what started as a lifeline, quickly blossomed into a global network connecting chefs and hospitality professionals with private households in need of talent. HELM extends the reach of Executive Chefs At Home&mdash;affording its members exclusive access to his elite culinary peers.
        </p>
      </div>

