        <p class="text-xs leading-relaxed text-charcoal/70" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">
          From an early age, hospitality was not simply a career path for Joseph Busone&mdash;it was a familial legacy. Raised in New York, within a family that owned celebrated Italian restaurants, a catering service, and nightclub lounge, Joe grew up immersed in the artistry, operational execution, and environmental warmth that embody exceptional service. From this foundation, an intuitive understanding of what it means to create meaningful experiences for guests became instinct.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xs leading-relaxed text-charcoal/70 mt-2" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">
          Joe began his career working in private suite hospitality at Arizona&rsquo;s premier sporting arenas and ballparks. He later moved to Las Vegas, where he assumed a departmental leadership role and was instrumental in opening the prestigious ARIA Resort &amp; Casino, and effectively managed its high-roller events and major convention operations. Joe then embarked on his entrepreneurial journey, co-founding an entertainment dining concept with 7 locations spanning multiple states. In 2021, he partnered with longtime friend, Brian Arruda, to scale Executive Chefs At Home from a boutique private chef placement agency to a global provider of luxury hospitality services. HELM is the latest chapter in Joe&rsquo;s illustrious high-end hospitality services career.
        </p>
